Represents a collection of people organized together into a community or other social, commercial or political structure. The group has some common purpose or reason for existence which goes beyond the set of people belonging to it and can act as an Agent. Organizations are often decomposable into hierarchical structures.

Group of Lines can be used to define several kinds of PT networks and sub-networks: what is usually called a Â‘public transport networkÂ’ is in fact only a specific GroupOfLines and a Line may belong to several of them.

The PassingTimes that are the result of the scheduling process and to be published in a timetable are called TimeTabledPassingTimes. 

The TimeTabledPassingTimes are normally generated a long time before the day of operation and are valid over a long period of time (e.g. summer, winter timetable)
Number of days after the starting time of the journey if not same calendar day. Default is 0 for same day.

Provides the specification of codes assigned to particular Vehicle Journeys when operated by Traibs of Compound Trains according to a functional purpose (passenger information, operation follow-up, etc.).
An alternative optimised representation of an Operating Period that uses a string of bits to indicate to which days with the period a specific DayType applies.
Days of week to which correspond the (up to first seven) bits.
String of bits (built of "0" and "1"), one for each day in the period: whether valid or not valid on the day.

usage.en: Normally there will be a bit for every day between start and end date. If bit is missing, assume available.

description.en: A VehicleJourney is the defined movement of a vehicle using a specified Journey Pattern on a particular Route. By virtue of being defined for a Day Type, a Vehicle Journey is a class of journeys that would take place at the same time on each day of a specified Day Type.

Day Type on which the Vehicle Journey is worked.
